** About Careview **

Careview is at the forefront of disability software solutions in Australia,
revolutionizing care with our comprehensive web and mobile platforms. Trusted
by over 700 organizations nationwide to support more than 150,000 NDIS
Participants, we are deeply committed to enhancing service delivery for
Australians living with disabilities through innovative technology.

** The Role **

As a Senior Software Engineer at Careview, you will play a pivotal role in
advancing our B2B SaaS platforms. With a focus on .NET Core, this full-time
position offers a dynamic blend of development, from APIs to microservices,
all within an Azure-centric environment. Whether you're in Brisbane or the
Gold Coast, we provide the flexibility to suit your lifestyle, coupled with
the opportunity to occasionally collaborate in person at our Gold Coast
office.

** What You'll Do **

  * Focus on enhancing our platform's backend services using .NET Core. Your work will directly impact our service's efficiency and scalability. 
  * Build robust APIs for effective communication with front-end applications and integration with distributed microservices architecture. 
  * Use Azure SDKs for developing backend features that interact with Azure services, emphasizing secure, scalable, and maintainable solutions. 
  * Write clean, maintainable code supported by comprehensive unit and integration tests to maintain high-quality standards. 
  * Work closely with the frontend team and other backend developers to ensure seamless integration and optimal performance of our applications. 
  * Use Entity Framework Core for data access and tools like ReSharper to enhance code quality and development efficiency. 

** About You **

  * A technology enthusiast passionate about solving complex business challenges. 
  * Comfortable navigating and enhancing a modern code base and greenfield projects. 
  * Proficient in ASP.NET Core, C#, and Entity Framework. 
  * Skilled in writing SQL queries and developing against Azure cloud resources. 
  * Eager to learn and adapt, with a strong foundation in test-driven development. 
  * A collaborative team player with excellent communication skills. 
  * Legally entitled to work in Australia, with a preference for candidates who can flexibly work between home and our Gold Coast office when needed. 
  * Extensive experience (5+ years) with the .NET ecosystem, with emphasis on ASP.NET Core and C#. 
  * Proven background in SQL Server / Entity framework and Azure cloud services. 
  * Familiarity with CI/CD practices and processes. 
  * Strong commitment to quality, maintainable, and tested code. 
  * Willing to learn new technologies, implement best practices, and write fault tolerant and robust code. 

** Experience Required **

  * 5+ Years of experience in .NET development (ASP.NET / Core and C#). 
  * 5+ Years of experience with Entity Framework / Core. 
  * 3+ API Development, RESTful APIs. 
  * Experience in test-driven development, including unit and integration tests. 
  * Experience with Azure cloud resources and distributed architecture. 
  * Unlimited full working rights in Australia required. 

** Join Us **

At Careview, you'll find a supportive community that values your contributions
and is eager to see you grow. If you're ready to make a tangible difference in
the lives of Australians living with disabilities, we'd love to hear from you.

Please note that recruitment agencies will not be considered.

